PRIVACY POLICY
All in One Calculator
Last Updated :
03rd Nov 2023
K D Infotech ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our All in One Calculator (the "App").
By using the App, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use the App.
Let's be transparent here. This application primarily functions as a calculator, and it does collect some non-personally identifiable data related to analytics and crash reporting to aid in the app's development and to address any potential issues. Additionally, you may come across advertisements within the app.
Should you opt to sign in, your settings and calculator history will be securely stored in a cloud-based database, associated solely with an account ID. We do not retain your personal information, such as your name and email; this data remains strictly on your device.
This webpage serves as an informative resource for visitors to our website and app, outlining our policies concerning the gathering, utilization, and disclosure of Personal Information when someone opts to utilize our Service.
By opting to use our Service, you are consenting to the collection and utilization of information as delineated in this policy. The Personal Information we gather is employed for the purpose of enhancing and providing our Service. Your information will not be utilized or disclosed to any party, except as explicitly detailed in this Privacy Policy.
Information We Collect :
We receive and store any information you knowingly provide to us when you fill any online forms in the Mobile Application. You can choose not to provide us with certain information, but then you may not be able to take advantage of some of the Mobile Application's features.
Collection of non-personal information :
When you launch our Mobile Application, certain data is automatically collected by our servers based on the information your device transmits. This data may encompass details such as your device's IP address, geographical location, device name and model, operating system type and version, language preferences, searches made within our Mobile Application, access timestamps, and other relevant statistics.
Use of collected information
We may utilize the information we collect from you for various purposes, including but not limited to:
Personalizing your experience with our Mobile Application.
Enhancing and refining the functionality of our Mobile Application.
Improving customer service by promptly responding to customer queries and emails.
Managing and operating our Mobile Application and associated services.
identification of potential misuse cases and for generating statistical data on Mobile
Application traffic and usage. This statistical data is anonymized and aggregated, ensuring that it cannot be used to identify individual users of the system.
Children :
We are committed to not knowingly collecting any personal information from individuals under the age of 13. If you are under 13 years of age, we kindly request that you refrain from submitting any personal information via our Mobile Application or Service. We strongly encourage parents and legal guardians to actively supervise their children's internet activities and to help enforce this policy by instructing their children never to share personal information through our Mobile Application or Service without their explicit consent.
If you have reason to believe that a child under the age of 13 has provided personal information to us through our Mobile Application or Service, please get in touch with us immediately.
Advertisement :
We may feature online advertisements and share aggregated, non-identifying information regarding our users, which we collect during the registration process or through online surveys and promotions, with select advertisers. Please be assured that we do not disclose personally identifiable information about individual customers to advertisers. On occasion, we may leverage this aggregated and non-identifying information to deliver customized advertisements to specific target audiences.
Information security :
We secure information you provide on computer servers in a controlled, secure environment, protected from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. We maintain reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards in an effort to protect against unauthorized access, use, modification, and disclosure of personal information in its control and custody. However, no data transmission over the Internet or wireless network can be guaranteed. Therefore, while we strive to protect your personal information, you acknowledge that (i) there are security and privacy limitations of the Internet which are beyond our control; (ii) the security, integrity, and privacy of any and all information and data exchanged between you and our Mobile Application cannot be guaranteed; and (iii) any such information and data may be viewed or tampered with in transit by a third-party, despite best efforts.
Data Security Incident :
In the event that we become aware of a compromise in the security of the Mobile Application or the unauthorized disclosure of users' Personal Information due to external activities such as security breaches or fraudulent activities, we reserve the right to take appropriate measures, including but not limited to investigation, reporting, and cooperation with law enforcement authorities. If a data breach occurs, we will make reasonable efforts to notify affected individuals, especially if there is a reasonable risk of harm to users resulting from the breach or if legal requirements mandate notification. In such cases, we will post a notice within the Mobile Application.
Legal disclosure :
We may disclose any information we collect, use, or receive if it becomes necessary or is permitted by applicable laws, such as when we are required to comply with a subpoena or a similar legal process. We will also disclose information when we genuinely believe in good faith that such disclosure is essential to safeguard our rights, ensure your safety, or the safety of others, investigate potential fraudulent activities, or respond to requests from government authorities.
Changes and amendments :
We retain the right to amend this privacy policy concerning the Mobile Application and Services at any time. Any modifications will be effective upon the posting of an updated version of this Policy within the Mobile Application. The updated date at the bottom of this page will be revised when changes are made. Your continued use of the Mobile Application following any such modifications will signify your acceptance of these changes.
Acceptance of this policy :
By using the Mobile Application or its Services, you acknowledge that you have read and consent to all the terms and conditions outlined in this Policy. Your usage of the Mobile Application and its Services signifies your agreement to be bound by this Policy. If you do not agree to comply with the terms set forth in this Policy, you are not authorized to use or access the Mobile Application and its Services.
Contacting us :
